      p Come back soon for an area to download all the photos you see here, see some new photos, and upload any photos you have or may take of us!
    section#faq
      h2.forever-full.bkgd-red: span #{text['index.nav.faq']}
      dl.faq
        dt.heading Are you registered anywhere?
        dd Gifts are certainly not necessary &mdash; just your presence as we celebrate is enough for us! Though there’s no need for gifts, we can appreciate that gifting is a primary love language for many of the people we care about. We’ve come up with some options for those folks:
          ul
            li contribute to the <a href="https://www.centreforeffectivealtruism.org/donate/">Center for Effective Altruism</a> in our honor
            li our <a href="https://www.blueprintregistry.com/registry/sarah-and-michail">travel fund/registry</a>
        dd If you’re going to simply trust your instincts on this one, we ask that you consider our upcoming travel adventures, as we’ll be putting most of our existing possessions in storage.
        dt.heading Can I bring a date?
        dd Your invite will specify whether there's a plus one for you! If you're unsure, please let us know!
        dt.heading Are kids welcome?
        dd Absolutely! If your invite was addressed to "The Whoever Family," then your kids are 100% welcome to join us.
        dt.heading Where should I park?
        dd For the ceremony, there will be parking inside the park.
        dd For the reception, there's a parking structure diagonally across from The Box which will be the most convenient place to park. We got a deal on a reduced cost for the structure, so let the attendant know you're here for an event at The Box!
        dt.heading What should I wear?
        dd Clothes! Casual, dressy casual, semi-formal &mdash; it's all the same to us! Maybe don't wear a tuxedo, or you might be uncomfortable. We also ask that you leave your white suits and dresses at home for this one.
        dt.heading Whom should I call with questions?
        dd Contact Sarah (262-227-7987) or Michail (414-574-1755) with any questions that might come up.
        dt.heading I am coming from out of town. Where should I stay?
        dd Wherever you want! We’re not reserving any rooms any place, but we’re happy to help you find someplace to stay! We’ve got family and friends in the area that are happy to host our guests, otherwise we’d recommend AirBnB or one of the hotels in the Milwaukee area.
